Q: By himself, Jack can clean a yacht in 12 hours. On a particular day, he happens to finish two-thirds of the work. The remaining portion of the work is done by Jill, whose rate of cleaning is just 5% of what Jack can do. How long does it take Jill to finish the remaining work?
Options: (a) 4 (b) 8 (c) 22 (d) 50 (e) 20
A:
 Jack can clean the yacht in 12 hours, so his rate is 1/12 of the yacht per hour. So, he can clean 2/3 of the yacht in 12 * 2/3 = 8 hours. So, the remaining part is 1/3 of the yacht, which he can clean in 12 * 1/3 = 4 hours. Jill can clean 1/20 of the yacht in 1 hour, so she can clean 1/20 * 4 = 1/5 of the yacht in 4 hours. So, it will take her 4 * 5 = 20 hours to clean the remaining part of the yacht. So, the answer is (e).

