Options: (a) 3 hours (b) 5 hours (c) 6 hours (d) 4 hours (e) 7 hours
A:
 The relative speed of the two cars is 55 - 52 = 3 mph. So, the distance between them will increase at a rate of 3 mph. The distance between them will be 15 miles when the time taken by the faster car to cover this distance is 15/3 = 5 hours. So the answer is (b).

