 Let the length of the sheet be x and the width be y. When the sheet is folded along one set of sides, the perimeter is 2x + 2y = 48. When the sheet is folded along the other set of sides, the perimeter is 2x + 2y = 66. So, 2x + 2y = 48 and 2x + 2y = 66. Solving these two equations, we get x = 12 and y = 20. So, the area of the sheet is 12 * 20 = 240. So the answer is not in the given options. So, the answer is (None of the above).

